title: Presto Pasta Night #14
summary: Presto Pasta Night #14 is a pescatarian recipe with 3 servings. For $17.42 per serving, this recipe covers 65% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. This main course has 1737 calories, 215g of protein, and 25g of fat per serving. 1 person were impressed by this recipe. A mixture of something like new zealand cod, sprinkle over, perfect, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so tasty. To use up the bread crumbs you could follow this main course with the Chocolate Banana Bread as a dessert. With a spoonacular score of 83%, this dish is outstanding. Try Presto Pasta, Bacon Tomato Presto Pasta, and Pork Ragu (Plus Pasta Night) for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: No one wine will suit every pasta dish. Pasta in a tomato-based sauce will usually work well with a medium-bodied red, such as a montepulciano or chianti. Pasta with seafood or pesto will fare better with a light-bodied white, such as a pinot grigio. Cheese-heavy pasta can pair well with red or white - you might try a sangiovese wine for hard cheeses and a chardonnay for soft cheeses. We may be able to make a better recommendation if you ask again with a specific pasta dish.
